SUMMARY:Service Sunday
DESCRIPTION:This is the Sunday where we join in work projects around our community as we BE the church! There are multiple service project locations around Magnolia with projects ranging from making blankets for kids entering foster care to habitat restoration! Afterwards\, we will all meet in MUCC’s Pilgrim Hall for cocoa and soup. Some locations have limited spots so register here today! \nHere is the list of this year’s Projects: \n\nProject Linus: Upstairs in Pilgrim Hall we will have a team that will make fleece blankets for kids going into Foster Care.  No sewing experience required!  This project is great for folks of all ages.\nMagnolia Park Habitat Restoration: The team will work under the direction of Seattle Green to remove aggressive weeds and maintain areas where weeds have been removed.  All equipment provided.\nDiscovery Park Habitat Restoration: The team at Discovery Park will be doing outdoor habitat restoration.  All equipment provided.\nSeattle Animal Shelter: The team at SAS will be doing projects in service of sheltered animals (Children must be 12+ and have adult supervision).\nBookmarks for Inmates for Hagar’s Ministry: The team will making bookmarks at MUCC in the Parlor for women at the Washington Corrections Center for Women.\nBallard Food Bank Hygiene Repack Prep: The team (working at Magnolia Presbyterian) will help to repack bulk Hygiene\, Pet\, and Dry Foods into smaller packages so that the Food Bank can keep its shelves stocked with these much needed items.\nDaybreak Star Cultural Center: Working at the Daybreak Star Cultural Center at Discovery Park\, participants at this site will be involved in outdoor gardening\, restoration and help with landscaping projects around the Center and in their Elder Garden.
URL:https://discovermagnolia.org/event/service-sunday/
LOCATION:Magnolia United Church of Christ\, 3555 W McGraw St\, Seattle\, WA\, 98199\, United States
CATEGORIES:Volunteering
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://discovermagnolia.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/servicesunday.png
END:VEVENT
