SUMMARY:Business Over Lunch
DESCRIPTION:Know Your Customer\, Grow Your Community: How to Attract\, Serve\, and Keep the Right Audience \nOrder your tickets HERE! \nTopic Description:\nUnderstanding your audience is the foundation of effective marketing\, sales\, and customer experience—but many small business owners are still trying to speak to “everyone.” This session helps entrepreneurs clearly identify who their ideal customer is\, what they truly need\, and how to connect with them in an authentic way. Attendees will leave with clarity and confidence to align their messaging\, offers\, and outreach with the people they’re best equipped to serve. \nWhy Attend (Value Points): \n\nClarify who your ideal customer actually is—and who they are not\nIdentify customer pain points that drive buying decisions\nStrengthen your messaging so it resonates instead of getting ignored\nBuild deeper trust and loyalty with the right audience\nImprove marketing results without increasing your budget\nReduce overwhelm by focusing your efforts more strategically\nAlign your products or services with real customer needs\nIncrease referrals by serving a clearly defined community\n\nGain confidence in how you show up and communicate your value
URL:https://discovermagnolia.org/event/business-over-lunch/
LOCATION:Aegis Living at Rodgers Park\, 2900 3rd Ave W\, Seattle\, WA\, 98119\, United States
CATEGORIES:Education,Food,Networking
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://discovermagnolia.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/BusinessOverLunch_BB21.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Magnolia Chamber of Commerce":MAILTO:info@discovermagnolia.org
END:VEVENT
